Open the **Item Card** of each grape item you vinify. In the **Vinification** group set the
output items that this grape produces and the calculation factors.

### Output item mapping

For the grape item, point each output to the corresponding item:

- **Stems**, **Destemmed Grape**, **Grape Pomace**, **Grape Must**, **Fermenting Wine**,
  **Wine Lees**, **Finished Wine**, **Reserve Wine**, **Downgraded Wine**, **Treated Grape Must**.

When you later select this grape on a vinification document, these output items are
copied automatically into the document.

### Calculation percentages

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Yield %** | Expected percentage of grape must or wine obtained from the total grape mass. |
| **Surplus %** | Expected percentage of cellar surplus produced beyond the standard yield. |
| **Stems %** | Expected percentage of the grape mass consisting of stems. |
| **Grape Pomace %** | Expected percentage of grape pomace remaining after pressing. |

### Date calculation formulas

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Vinification Date Calculation** | Date formula (e.g. `7D`) added to the document date to obtain the vinification date. |
| **Fermentation Date Calculation** | Date formula added to the document date to obtain the fermentation date. |
| **Wine Prod. Date Calculation** | Date formula added to the document date to obtain the wine production date. |

### White vs. red wine

The grape item's **Vinification Type** (White or Red) determines processing rules. The
**Coal Treatment** option on a vinification is only available for **white** grapes.

### Lot number generation

To auto-generate lot numbers for output items, configure on each output item either:

- a **Lot No. Formula** (EOS WINE lot formula), or
- a **Lot Nos.** number series.